WebQL pagination extracts data across multiple pages:

```json
{
  "@url": "https://quotes.toscrape.com/",
  "@steps": [
    {
      "@xpath": "//div[@class='quote']",
      "@fields": {
        "text": ".//span[@class='text']/text()",
        "author": ".//small[@class='author']/text()"
      }
    }
  ],
  "@pagination": {
    "@xpath": "//li[@class='next']/a/@href",
    "@limit": 3
  }
}
```

**How it works**:
- `@xpath` finds the "next page" link
- `@limit` controls how many pages to process
- Automatically follows links and extracts data from each page

WebQL @follow navigates to linked pages for deeper extraction:

```json
{
  "@url": "https://example.com/listings",
  "@steps": [
    {
      "@xpath": "//div[@class='item']",
      "@fields": {
        "title": ".//h3/text()"
      },
      "@follow": {
        "@xpath": ".//a[@class='details']/@href",
        "@max-depth": 2,
        "@steps": [
          {
            "@xpath": "//div[@class='details']",
            "@fields": {
              "description": ".//p/text()",
              "price": ".//span[@class='price']/text()"
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

**Key features**:
- @max-depth: Limits how deep to follow links
- @detect-cycles: Prevents infinite loops
- @follow-external: Controls external domain following
